This paper discusses the evolution of cyber attacks and defenses, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed metric framework involves the use of quantitative metrics, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the dynamic nature of system behaviors, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SI). Finally, the paper focuses on cyber agility, which is a topic related to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
